                <note rend="inline" type="source">711.632/94a: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Austria</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stockton</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-02-24T17:00:00-05:00"
                            >February 24, 1931—5 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>9. Advice and consent of Senate to ratification of supplementary agreement given
                    February 20. Instrument of ratification of treaty and supplementary agreement
                    will be forwarded for exchange at Vienna upon advice by you by cable that
                    Austria is prepared to effect exchange.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
